description.narrative: Establish a common agenda for Asia-Pacific counties to invest in and empower youth to accelerate implementation of SDGs through leadership, social innovation and entrepreneurship.

condition.narrative: UNDP as the Implementing Partner will comply with the policies, procedures and practices of the United Nations Security Management System (UNSMS.)

description.narrative:
1.1. “Youth Empowerment Alliance of Incubators” (hereinafter the “Youth Alliance”) of business incubators, young entrepreneurs and social innovators established and launched at the Global Youth Forum
1.2. Secretariat for the Youth Alliance established
2.1. National and regional innovation challenges, events and forums convened to foster youth-led entrepreneurship to accelerate SDG implementation
3.1. A regional policy dialogue on youth innovation and entrepreneurship convened
4.1. Conduct research of existing networks of business incubators in the Asia-Pacific region to be incorporated into the Youth Alliance on a selective basis conducted (to support result 1.1.)
4.2. A report on the state of youth-led entrepreneurship, social innovation and leadership in the region in the context of SDGs published by the Youth Alliance
5.1. Partnerships mechanism developed in order to strengthen youth empowerment initiatives
5.2. A Youth Start-up Incubator scheme established to support youth entrepreneurs, with special focus given to young women and marginalized youth

comment.narrative:
1: “Youth Empowerment Alliance of Incubators” fosters and incubates youth-led entrepreneurship for achieving the SDGs (Incubators and Innovations)
2: Youth Leadership Initiative inspires and engages young people through innovation and localized actions for SDGs (Inspire and Engage)
3: Forums addressing Youth Leadership, Innovation and Entrepreneurship convened to set the agenda for Asia Pacific-wide initiatives on youth accelerating the SDGs (Network and Policy)
4: Research and knowledge exchange Initiative informs new youth entrepreneurship initiatives, including the work of the “Youth Empowerment Alliance of Incubators” (Knowledge)
5: Financial Action Initiative established to ensure financial sustainability of current and new youth empowerment initiatives (Sustainability)

1.1. “Youth Empowerment Alliance of Incubators” (hereinafter the “Youth Alliance”) of business incubators, young entrepreneurs and social innovators established and launched at the Global Youth Forum - Youth Empowerment Alliance of over 190 partners established and providing support to young entrepreneurs and social innovators across Asia Pacific.
1.2. Secretariat for the Youth Alliance established - Youth Empowerment Alliance established with capacity development support to core partners.
2.1. National and regional innovation challenges, events and forums convened to foster youth-led entrepreneurship to accelerate SDG implementation - National innovation challenges held in 26 countries in 2020 supporting youth entrepreneurs to accelerate SDG implementation.
3.3. A Regional Youth Summit on entrepreneurship and innovation convened - 3 regional summits on youth entrepreneurship, innovation and leadership convened.
5.2. A Youth Start-up Incubator scheme established to support youth entrepreneurs, with special focus given to young women and marginalized youth - $1.8 million in investment mobilised for youth-led social enterprises through the Youth Co:Lab Springboard incubation programme. Within 2020, the Springboard programme supported 133 youth-led businesses committed to achieving the SDGs across 23 countries in Asia and the Pacific.

1.1. “Youth Empowerment Alliance of Incubators” develops capacity of Youth Empowerment Alliance members - Youth Empowerment Alliance has built the capabilities of 202 partner organisations to strengthen the youth entrepreneurship ecosystem in Asia-Pacific.
2.1. National and regional innovation challenges, events and forums convened to foster youth-led entrepreneurship to accelerate SDG implementation - Youth Co:Lab conducted National Dialogues and innovation challenges in 28 markets across Asia-Pacific.
3.3. Regional Youth Summit on entrepreneurship and innovation convened - From 2-4 June 2021, Youth Co:Lab convened the Youth Co:Lab Virtual Summit 2021, reaching 9.5 million people and delivering a key milestone for the regional youth empowerment agenda.
5.2. Youth Start-up Incubator scheme supports youth entrepreneurs, with special focus given to young women and marginalized youth - Youth Co:Lab Regional Springboard incubator scheme provided dedicated support to 430 youth-led startups to strengthen their product market fit, access opportunities, and scale their revenue and impact against the SDGs.
